{
    "text": "Taking change for granted",
    "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 13:52:14 GMT",
    "type": "outline",
    "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted",
    "subs": [
        {
            "text": "Michel Foucault talked once about wanting to change and seeing his work as a process inevitably leading to change in himself. Schools, I suspect, rarely talk with young people about that sort of thing, rarely say, \"You'll want something new for yourself, you'll want to become better at something, more skillful, more free to play in an interesting field, more ready to make a life of your own choosing. Let's talk about the kinds of experiences and activities help a young person head out in that direction.\" (And why can't I remember teachers ever talking this way?)",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 13:52:15 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a135215"
        },
        {
            "text": "Here's the Foucault quotation, from an interview in a book called Politics, Philosophy, Culture:",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 13:54:55 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a135455",
            "subs": [
                {
                    "text": "That’s the reason also why, when people say, “Well, you thought this a few years ago and now you say something else,” my answer is, [Laughter] “Well, do you think I have worked like that all those years to say the same thing and not to be changed?” This transformation of one’s self by one’s own knowledge is, I think, something rather close to the aesthetic experience. Why should a painter work if he is not transformed by his own painting?",
                    "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:03:09 GMT",
                    "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a140309"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Interesting point he makes about the painter, too. No matter what we study, we bring into ourselves a new filter on the world, a new lens for seeing, a new set of terms and perceptions that make a portion of our experience easier to think about. Likely, too, we're making some things newly important and other things less important in our mind, installing better perceptual tools and also prejudices against thinking about this thing or that thing.",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:04:13 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a140413"
        },
        {
            "text": "That's one reason why a diverse education is vital, an education in which the tools of many disciplines and the experiences of many cultures become part of our experience.",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:12:28 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a141228"
        },
        {
            "text": "A career-only education makes a person both smarter and dumber.",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:14:16 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a141416"
        },
        {
            "text": "I used to ask first-year students something like this: \"At the end of your four years here, do you want to have spent all that tuition money and all that time and energy so you can be just the same as you were when you arrived, or different?\"",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:15:22 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a141522"
        },
        {
            "text": "Better would have been to also ask, \"What do you want to develop in yourself in these years? And why?\"",
            "created": "Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:17:33 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/24/135214.html?title=takingChangeForGranted#a141733"
        }
    ]
}

